iples &amp; Patterns?','How to avoid code duplication!  Principles & Patterns?','','publish','open','closed','','how-to-avoid-code-duplication-principles-patterns','','','2018-01-08 03:29:37','2018-01-08 03:29:37','',0,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/question/how-to-avoid-code-duplication-principles-patterns/',0,'question','',0),(83,4,'2018-01-08 03:29:37','2018-01-08 03:29:37','Your posted a question \"\" ','post_question','','publish','open','closed','','post_question-4','','','2018-01-08 03:29:37','2018-01-08 03:29:37','',82,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/changelog/post_question-4/',0,'changelog','',0),(84,4,'2018-01-08 03:34:18','2018-01-08 03:34:18','<h1>Code duplication</h1>\r\n<strong>1. What is code duplication</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Duplicate code is a computer programming term for a sequence of source code that occurs more than once, either within a program or across different programs owned or maintained by the same entity. - Wiki</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>2. Why it happen</strong>\r\n\r\nDuplication usually occurs when multiple programmers are working on different parts of the same program at the same time. Since they are working on different tasks, they may be unaware their colleague has already written similar code that could be repurposed for their own needs.\r\n\r\nThere is also more subtle duplication, when specific parts of code look different but actually perform the same job. This kind of duplication can be hard to find and fix.\r\n\r\nSometimes duplication is purposeful. When rushing to meet deadlines and the existing code is \"almost right\" for the job, novice programmers may not be able to resist the temptation of copying and pasting the relevant code. And in some cases, the programmer is simply too lazy to de-clutter.\r\n\r\n<strong>3. Why avoid code duplication</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>The way you get programmer productivity is not by increasing the lines of code per programmer per day. That doesnt work. The way you get programmer productivity is by eliminating lines of code you have to write.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>The line of code thats the fastest to write, that never breaks, that doesnt need maintenance, is the line you never had to write.</em>\r\n- Steve Jobs\r\n\r\n<b>Benefit:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Less Code to Write = Less Code to Maintain = More features delivered = More productive</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Improve code structure and design:</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Easier to understand</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Easier to modify</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Easier to add new features</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>4. Patterns Treatment</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>4.1 Extract Method</strong>\r\n\r\nUsed when duplicate code is found in two or more methods in the same class (or more function in scripts)\r\nExtract duplicate code into new function and call it in both places .\r\n\r\n<strong>4.2 Inheritance</strong>\r\n\r\nUsed when duplicate code is found in two different classes.\r\nMove duplicate code in classes into supper class. If not, then create it (as long as appropriate)\r\n\r\n<strong>4.3 Substitute Algorithm.</strong>\r\n\r\nUsed if two methods do the same thing but use different algorithms. Select the best algorithm and apply.\r\n\r\n<strong>4.4 Form Template Method</strong>\r\n\r\nUsed for the methods have same template.\r\n\r\n<strong>5. When to Ignore</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In very rare cases, merging two identical fragments of code can make the code less intuitive and obvious.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In test script.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://dzone.com/articles/testing-duplicate-code-your-te\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https://dzone.com/articles/testing-duplicate-code-your-te </span></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>6. Analyzing Duplicates in Pycharm (RubyMind, ...)</strong>\r\n\r\nPyCharm helps you find repetitive blocks of code in a certain range. This range can be a single file, a project, a module, or a custom scope. Results of analysis display in the dedicated tab of the Duplicates tool window.\r\n\r\n<strong>References:</strong>\r\nhttps://refactoring.guru/smells/duplicate-code\r\nhttps://www.jetbrains.com/help/pycharm/analyzing-duplicates.html\r\nhttps://www.slideshare.net/kindblad/avoid-code-duplication-principles-patterns\r\n\r\nSee more:https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Z2rRHlXXA7YgFrzNyVwJOMkU6nsBtcqxm7llWWdl0nw/edit#heading=h.7czqtlkw2d0j','RE: How to avoid code duplication!  Principles & Patterns?','','publish','open','closed','','re-how-to-avoid-code-duplication-principles-patterns','','','2018-01-08 03:34:18','2018-01-08 03:34:18','',82,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/answer/re-how-to-avoid-code-duplication-principles-patterns/',0,'answer','',0),(85,4,'2018-01-08 03:34:18','2018-01-08 03:34:18','You answered on question \"How to avoid code duplication!  Principles &#038; Patterns?\"','post_answer','','publish','open','closed','','post_answer-4','','','2018-01-08 03:34:18','2018-01-08 03:34:18','',84,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/changelog/post_answer-4/',0,'changelog','',0),(86,1,'2018-01-08 08:01:44','2018-01-08 08:01:44','Do vn  ngh mnh ch outsource lm xong ri \"phn\" v lun gn mc \" lm d n ln\" nhng suy ngh th cng ln nh ci h lm.','ti sao cc cng ty outsource t quan tm ti bo mt ni chung?','','publish','open','closed','','tai-sao-cac-cong-ty-outsourcing-it-quan-tam-toi-bao-mat-noi-chung','','','2018-01-08 08:17:31','2018-01-08 08:17:31','',0,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/question/tai-sao-cac-cong-ty-outsourcing-it-quan-tam-toi-bao-mat-noi-chung/',0,'question','',0),(87,1,'2018-01-08 08:01:44','2018-01-08 08:01:44','Your posted a question \"\" ','post_question','','publish'