:14:04','',128,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/changelog/q_vote_up-6/',0,'changelog','',0),(179,1,'2018-01-26 03:51:41','2018-01-26 03:51:41','Lin quan n k thut nhiu dev hoc manager gp phi dn n ch \"improved\" thng l khng c hi ktv thi gian l bin s quan trng nht trong ngnh cng ngh (s thay i rt nhanh v cng ngh v thi gian khng i ai)','Pattern & anti-Pattern khi p dng build t ng','','publish','open','closed','','pattern-anti-pattern-khi-ap-dung-build-tu-dong','','','2018-01-26 03:59:21','2018-01-26 03:59:21','',0,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/?post_type=question&#038;p=179',0,'question','',0),(180,1,'2018-01-26 03:51:36','2018-01-26 03:51:36','You question on question \"\" was edited','edit_question','','publish','open','closed','','edit_question-13','','','2018-01-26 03:51:36','2018-01-26 03:51:36','',179,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/changelog/edit_question-13/',0,'changelog','',0),(181,1,'2018-01-26 03:51:41','2018-01-26 03:51:41','Theo phn tch google trends lin quan n CI/CDTheo phn tch google trends lin quan n CI/CD\r\nhttps://dzone.com/storage/temp/5619859-picture1.pnghttps://dzone.com/storage/temp/5619860-picture2.png\r\n5 key qua trng trong CI/CD\r\n1.Better Quality Code 2.Better Tested Code 3.Production Snapshot 4.Early Error Detection 5.Project Confidence\r\n18 pattern &amp; anti-pattern CI/CD\r\nLin quan n k thut nhiu dev hoc manager gp phi dn n ch \"improved\" thng l khng c hi ktv thi gian l bin s quan trng nht trong ngnh cng ngh (s thay i rt nhanh v cng ngh v thi gian khng i ai)\r\nBuild Software at Every ChangePattern Run a software build with every change applied to the Repository.Anti-patterns Scheduled builds, nightly builds, building periodically, building exclusively on developer\'s machines, not building at all.\r\n--&gt; cc cng ty rt hay gp phi vn  ny, v cu ni ca ming hay gp phi\"mnh c th t build theo ngy hoc theo thng hoc theo tun ... v cui cng thng khng thnh cng\"\r\n\r\nVersion Control\r\nTask-Level Commit\r\ngit add -Agit commit -m \"message\" (i.e., git commit -m \"added file object class\")git pushPattern Organize source code changes by task-oriented units of work and submit changes as a Task-Level Commit.Anti-Patterns Keeping changes local to development for several days and stacking up changes until committing all changes. This often causes build failures or requires complex troubleshooting.\r\n--&gt; vn  ny th cng gp phi lin tc trong cc cng ty p dng qu trnh t ng (cu ni thng hay lcc d n thay i m task lm theo tun th sao m update theo ngy c -&gt; improved khng bao gi xut hin)\r\n\r\nLabel Build\r\ngit tag -a annotation -m \"message\" (i.e., git tag -a v1.2.12 -m \"version 1.2.12\")git push remote --tags\r\nPattern Tag or Label the build with unique name so that you can refer to run the same build at another time.Anti-Patterns Not labeling builds, using revisions or branches as \"labels.\"\r\n--&gt; vn  ny th cng gp phi do khng thng nht cch lm vic (thng th cu ni thng l uh c push ln cho h sa nhanh --&gt; khng c ch  message truyn t thng tin chnh xc cho tng commit)\r\nBuild Management\r\nAutomated Buildcurl http://yourserver/git/notifyCommit?url=&lt;URL of the Git repository&gt;[&amp;[,branch2]*][&amp;sha1=&lt;commit ID&gt;]\r\nPattern * Automate all activities to build software from a source without manual configuration.* Create build scripts that will be executed by a CI system so that software is built at every change.\r\nAnti-Patterns Continually repeating the same processes with manual builds or partially automated builds requiring numerous manual configuration activities.\r\n--&gt; ci ny th cng hay gp phi (cu ni thng l em lm template ri ci kia lm tng t nu lm th s ra  sa bng tay ri chy tip vy t ng li thnh manual mt ri)\r\nBuild Practices\r\nPre-Merge Build\r\ngulp &lt;my project&gt;\r\nPattern Verify that your changes will not break the integration build by performing a pre-merge buildeither locally or using Continuous Integration.Anti-Patterns Checking in changes to a version-control repository without running a build on a developer\'s workstation.\r\n--&gt; cu ni hay xut hin l \"pull khng phi l  review code m dng 1 tool no  \" pull khng phi l  review nhng bn cht n l  build for review trong hnh ng pre-merge trc khi code OK\r\nContinuous Feedback\r\nPattern Send automated feedback from the CI server to development team members involved in the build.Anti-Patterns Sending minimal feedback that provides no insight into the build failure or is non-actionable. Sending too much feedback, including to team members uninvolved with the build. This is eventually treated like spam, which causes people to ignore messages.\r\n--&gt; ci ny cng kh hay xy ra do qu trnh qun l khng c hoc khng c quan tm dn ti cc message build tr thnh spam n khng quan trng i vi ngi nhn thng tin d n cu ni thng l \" lm c notify ri \" nhng quan trng notify cho ai v thng tin cn truyn t l g\r\nExpeditious Fixes\r\nPattern Fix build errors as soon as they occur.Anti-Patterns Allowing problems to stack up (build entropy) or waiting for them to be fixed in future builds.\r\n--&gt; cu ni thng ca dev hoc leader \"sa c 1 t hoc i bn sa ca ngi khc  bn mi ri up ln 1 th khng mt thi gian v n nh nht , lt vt\"\r\nDeveloper DocumentationPattern Generate developer documentation with builds based on checked-in source code.Anti-Patterns Manually generating developer documentation. This is both a burdensome process and one in which the information becomes useless quickly because it does not reflect the checked-in source code.\r\n--&gt; thng l ti liu d n nh swagger chng hn --&gt; khng vit trc tip trong code m thng vit ngoi file ti liu ring\r\nBuild ConfigurationIndependent Build\r\nPattern Create build scripts that are decoupled from IDEs, but can be invoked by an IDE. These build scripts will be executed by a CI system as well so that software is built at every change.Anti-Patterns Relying on IDE settings for Automated Build. Build cannot run from the command line.\r\n--&gt;\r\nSingle Command\r\nPattern Ensure all build processes can be run through a single command.Anti-Patterns Requiring people or servers to enter multiple commands and procedures in the deployment process, such as copying files, modifying configuration files, restarting a server, setting passwords, and other repetitive, error-prone actions.\r\n--&gt; ci ny hu ht cng ty gp phi, thi lm 1 ci hoc khng gi cho mi vic n gin m a ra rt nhiu th lm cho vic t ng tr thnh ri rm phc tp \"cu ni thng l ci ny kh lm no l copy no l cu hnh\" ci cn l 1 cu lnh hoc 1 nt click v khng quan tm ti g na\r\nDedicated Resources\r\nPattern Run master builds on a separate dedicated machine or cloud service.Anti-Patterns Relying on existing environmental and configuration assumptions (can lead to the \"but it works on my machine problem\").\r\n---&gt; khi  chy th bt c mi trng no cng phi chy ging nhau ch khng c l do \" sao my em deploy chy ca anh th khng???\"\r\nExternalize and Tokenize ConfigurationPattern * Externalize all variable values from the application configuration into build-time properties.* Use tokens so the build process knows where to add variable values.\r\nAnti-Patterns Hardcoding values in configuration files or using GUI tools to do the same.\r\n--&gt; khng c cu hnh file cho cc mi trng hoc s dng GUI khng hiu bn cht hoc hardcode ngay cho vic build\r\nDatabaseScripting Database Changes\r\nPattern All changes made to a database during development should be recorded into database scripts that can be run on every database on every platform hosting the project (including developer machines, see below).Anti-Patterns Expecting database administrators to manually compare databases between platforms for changes, or to create on-off scripts that are only good for updating a single platform.\r\n--&gt; vic deploy database khng c script trong cc phin bn hay backup lm bng tay khi dng li h thng v li quay li cu ni \"ci ny phc tp v kh , phin bn ny th phi lm thm ci ny , database ny cha  thiu trng ny.....\"\r\nDatabase Sandbox\r\nPattern * Create a lightweight version of your database (only enough records to test functionality)* Use a command line interface to populate the local database sandboxes for each developer, tester, and build server* Use this data in development environments to expedite test execution\r\nAnti-Patterns Sharing development database.\r\n--&gt; ci ny th cng kh thng xuyn xy ra\r\nUpdate Scripts Stored In The VCS\r\nPattern Store the scripts for updating the database and its data in the version control system with the code and annotate appropriatelyAnti-Patterns Storing update scripts in an alternative location, i.e. a shared file serverTesting and Code Quality--&gt; ...\r\nAutomated Tests\r\nPattern Write automated tests for each code path, both success testing and failure testing.Anti-Patterns * Not running tests\r\n* No regression testing\r\n* Manual testing\r\n--&gt; 1 s cng ty khng p dng test nn khng  cp\r\nBuild Quality ThresholdPattern * Notify team members of code aberrations such as low code coverage or the use of coding anti-patterns.* Fail a build when a project rule is violated.* Use continuous feedback mechanisms to notify team members.\r\nAnti-Patterns * Deep dive reviews of every code change.* Manually calculating or guesstimating code coverage.\r\n--&gt; ...\r\nAutomated Smoke TestPattern Create smoke tests that can be used by CI servers, developers, QA, and testing as a pre-check to confirm the most important functionality as they work, or before committing resources to a full build.\r\nAnti-Patterns * Manually running functional tests.\r\n* Forcing QA to run the full suite before every session\r\n* Manually checking deployment sensitive sections of the project\r\n--&gt; ....\r\n\r\nTt c thng tin trn c tham kho t cun sch ny vi cc d n p dng thc t\r\nhttps://www.amazon.com/Software-Configuration-Management-Patterns-Integration/dp/B010ILCQ5M','Pattern & anti-Pattern khi p dng build t ng','','inherit','closed','closed','','179-revision-v1','','','2018-01-26 03:51:41','2018-01-26 03:51:41','',179,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/2018/01/26/179-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(182,1,'2018-01-26 03:51:41','2018-01-26 03:51:41','You question on question \"Pattern &#038; anti-Pattern khi p dng build t ng\" was edited','edit_question','','publish','open','closed','','edit_question-14','','','2018-01-26 03:51:41','2018-01-26 03:51:41','',179,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/changelog/edit_question-14/',0,'changelog','',0),(183,1,'2018-01-26 03:52:31','2018-01-26 03:52:31','test','Pattern & anti-Pattern khi p dng build t ng','','inherit','closed','closed','','179-revision-v1','','','2018-01-26 03:52:31','2018-01-26 03:52:31','',179,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/2018/01/26/179-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(184,1,'2018-01-26 03:52:31','2018-01-26 03:52:31','You question on question \"\" was edited','edit_question','','publish','open','closed','','edit_question-15','','','2018-01-26 03:52:31','2018-01-26 03:52:31','',179,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/changelog/edit_question-15/',0,'changelog','',0),(185,1,'2018-01-26 03:53:16','2018-01-26 03:53:16','<p>Theo phn tch google trends lin quan n CI/CDTheo phn tch google trends lin quan n CI/CD</p><p><img src=\"https://dzone.com/storage/temp/5619859-picture1.png\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://dzone.com/storage/temp/5619860-picture2.png\" /></p><p><strong>5 key qua trng trong CI/CD</strong></p><p>1.Better Quality Code : kt qu cui cng l cht lng khi t ng th khng ph thuc vo cm gic m ph thuc vo s lng nh lng</p><p>2.Better Tested Code : quan tm hn ti vic test</p><p>3.Production Snapshot : bt k khi no cng c 1 phin bn hon chnh sm cho vic th nghim cho production</p><p>4.Early Error Detection : rt quan trng v phng bnh sm hn cha bnh</p><p>5.Project Confidence : d n bo mt hn khi cc thnh phn thng tin mt khu h thng hoc d n ra sao cc key s dng cho cc nhnh</p><p><strong>18 pattern &amp; anti-pattern CI/CD</strong></p><p>Build Software at Every Change</p><p>Pattern Run a software build with every change applied to the Repository.</p><p>Anti-patterns Scheduled builds, nightly builds, building periodically, building exclusively on developer\'s machines, not building at all.</p><p>--&gt; cc cng ty rt hay gp phi vn  ny, v cu ni ca ming hay gp phi\"mnh c th t build theo ngy hoc theo thng hoc theo tun ... v cui cng thng khng thnh cng\"</p><p>Version Control<br />Task-Level Commit<br />git add -Agit commit -m \"message\" (i.e., git commit -m \"added file object class\")</p><p>git push</p><p>Pattern Organize source code changes by task-oriented units of work and submit changes as a Task-Level Commit.</p><p>Anti-Patterns Keeping changes local to development for several days and stacking up changes until committing all changes. This often causes build failures or requires complex troubleshooting.</p><p>--&gt; vn  ny th cng gp phi lin tc trong cc cng ty p dng qu trnh t ng (cu ni thng hay lcc d n thay i m task lm theo tun th sao m update theo ngy c -&gt; improved khng bao gi xut hin)</p><p>Label Build<br />git tag -a annotation -m \"message\" (i.e., git tag -a v1.2.12 -m \"version 1.2.12\")git push remote --tags</p><p>Pattern Tag or Label the build with unique name so that you can refer to run the same build at another time.</p><p>Anti-Patterns Not labeling builds, using revisions or branches as \"labels.\"<br />--&gt; vn  ny th cng gp phi do khng thng nht cch lm vic (thng th cu ni thng l uh c push ln cho h sa nhanh --&gt; khng c ch  message truyn t thng tin chnh xc cho tng commit)</p><p>Build Management</p><p>Automated Build</p><p>curl http://yourserver/git/notifyCommit?url=&lt;URL of the Git repository&gt;[&amp;[,branch2]*][&amp;sha1=&lt;commit ID&gt;]</p><p>Pattern * Automate all activities to build software from a source without manual configuration.* Create build scripts that will be executed by a CI system so that software is built at every change.</p><p>Anti-Patterns Continually repeating the same processes with manual builds or partially automated builds requiring numerous manual configuration activities.</p><p>--&gt; ci ny th cng hay gp phi (cu ni thng l em lm template ri ci kia lm tng t nu lm th s ra  sa bng tay ri chy tip vy t ng li thnh manual mt ri)</p><p>Build Practices</p><p>Pre-Merge Build</p><p>gulp &lt;my project&gt;</p><p>Pattern Verify that your changes will not break the integration build by performing a pre-merge buildeither locally or using Continuous Integration.</p><p>Anti-Patterns Checking in changes to a version-control repository without running a build on a developer\'s workstation.</p><p>--&gt; cu ni hay xut hin l \"pull khng phi l  review code m dng 1 tool no  \" pull khng phi l  review nhng bn cht n l  build for review trong hnh ng pre-merge trc khi code OK</p><p>Continuous Feedback</p><p>Pattern Send automated feedback from the CI server to development team members involved in the build</p><p>Anti-Patterns Sending minimal feedback that provides no insight into the build failure or is non-actionable. Sending too much feedback, including to team members uninvolved with the build. This is eventually treated like spam, which causes people to ignore messages.</p><p>--&gt; ci ny cng kh hay xy ra do qu trnh qun l khng c hoc khng c quan tm dn ti cc message build tr thnh spam n khng quan trng i vi ngi nhn thng tin d n cu ni thng l \" lm c notify ri \" nhng quan trng notify cho ai v thng tin cn truyn t l g</p><p>Expeditious Fixes</p><p>Pattern Fix build errors as soon as they occur.</p><p>Anti-Patterns Allowing problems to stack up (build entropy) or waiting for them to be fixed in future builds.</p><p>--&gt; cu ni thng ca dev hoc leader \"sa c 1 t hoc i bn sa ca ngi khc  bn mi ri up ln 1 th khng mt thi gian v n nh nht , lt vt\"</p><p>Developer Documentation</p><p>Pattern Generate developer documentation with builds based on checked-in source code.</p><p>Anti-Patterns Manually generating developer documentation. This is both a burdensome process and one in which the information becomes useless quickly because it does not reflect the checked-in source code.</p><p>--&gt; thng l ti liu d n nh swagger chng hn --&gt; khng vit trc tip trong code m thng vit ngoi file ti liu ring</p><p>Build ConfigurationIndependent Build</p><p>Pattern Create build scripts that are decoupled from IDEs, but can be invoked by an IDE. These build scripts will be executed by a CI system as well so that software is built at every change.</p><p>Anti-Patterns Relying on IDE settings for Automated Build. Build cannot run from the command line.<br />--&gt; ....</p><p>Single Command</p><p>Pattern Ensure all build processes can be run through a single command.</p><p>Anti-Patterns Requiring people or servers to enter multiple commands and procedures in the deployment process, such as copying files, modifying configuration files, restarting a server, setting passwords, and other repetitive, error-prone actions.</p><p>--&gt; ci ny hu ht cng ty gp phi, thi lm 1 ci hoc khng gi cho mi vic n gin m a ra rt nhiu th lm cho vic t ng tr thnh ri rm phc tp \"cu ni thng l ci ny kh lm no l copy no l cu hnh\" ci cn l 1 cu lnh hoc 1 nt click v khng quan tm ti g na</p><p>Dedicated Resources</p><p>Pattern Run master builds on a separate dedicated machine or cloud service.</p><p>Anti-Patterns Relying on existing environmental and configuration assumptions (can lead to the \"but it works on my machine problem\").</p><p>---&gt; khi  chy th bt c mi trng no cng phi chy ging nhau ch khng c l do \" sao my em deploy chy ca anh th khng???\"</p><p>Externalize and Tokenize Configuration</p><p>Pattern * Externalize all variable values from the application configuration into build-time properties.* Use tokens so the build process knows where to add variable values.</p><p>Anti-Patterns Hardcoding values in configuration files or using GUI tools to do the same.</p><p>--&gt; khng c cu hnh file cho cc mi trng hoc s dng GUI khng hiu bn cht hoc hardcode ngay cho vic build</p><p>DatabaseScripting Database Changes</p><p>Pattern All changes made to a database during development should be recorded into database scripts that can be run on every database on every platform hosting the project (including developer machines, see below).</p><p>Anti-Patterns Expecting database administrators to manually compare databases between platforms for changes, or to create on-off scripts that are only good for updating a single platform.</p><p>--&gt; vic deploy database khng c script trong cc phin bn hay backup lm bng tay khi dng li h thng v li quay li cu ni \"ci ny phc tp v kh , phin bn ny th phi lm thm ci ny , database ny cha  thiu trng ny.....\"</p><p>Database Sandbox</p><p>Pattern * Create a lightweight version of your database (only enough records to test functionality)* Use a command line interface to populate the local database sandboxes for each developer, tester, and build server* Use this data in development environments to expedite test execution</p><p>Anti-Patterns Sharing development database.</p><p>--&gt; ci ny th cng kh thng xuyn xy ra</p><p>Update Scripts Stored In The VCS</p><p>Pattern Store the scripts for updating the database and its data in the version control system with the code and annotate appropriately</p><p>Anti-Patterns Storing update scripts in an alternative location, i.e. a shared file serverTesting and Code Quality</p><p>--&gt; ...</p><p>Automated Tests</p><p>Pattern Write automated tests for each code path, both success testing and failure testing</p><p>Anti-Patterns * Not running tests<br />* No regression testing<br />* Manual testing</p><p>--&gt; 1 s cng ty khng p dng test nn khng  cp</p><p>Build Quality Threshold</p><p>Pattern * Notify team members of code aberrations such as low code coverage or the use of coding anti-patterns.* Fail a build when a project rule is violated.* Use continuous feedback mechanisms to notify team members.</p><p>Anti-Patterns * Deep dive reviews of every code change.* Manually calculating or guesstimating code coverage.<br />--&gt; ...</p><p>Automated Smoke Test</p><p>Pattern Create smoke tests that can be used by CI servers, developers, QA, and testing as a pre-check to confirm the most important functionality as they work, or before committing resources to a full build.</p><p>Anti-Patterns * Manually running functional tests.</p><p>* Forcing QA to run the full suite before every session<br />* Manually checking deployment sensitive sections of the project<br />--&gt; ....</p><p>Tt c thng tin trn c tham kho t cun sch ny vi cc d n p dng thc t<br />https://www.amazon.com/Software-Configuration-Management-Patterns-Integration/dp/B010ILCQ5M</p>','RE: Pattern & anti-Pattern khi p dng build t ng','','publish','open','closed','','re-pattern-anti-pattern-khi-ap-dung-build-tu-dong','','','2018-01-26 04:02:55','2018-01-26 04:02:55','',179,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/answer/re-pattern-anti-pattern-khi-ap-dung-build-tu-dong/',0,'answer','',1),(186,1,'2018-01-26 03:53:16','2018-01-26 03:53:16','You answered on question \"Pattern &#038; anti-Pattern khi p dng build t ng\"','post_answer','','publish','open','closed','','post_answer-15','','','2018-01-26 03:53:16','2018-01-26 03:53:16','',185,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/changelog/post_answer-15/',0,'changelog','',0),(187,1,'2018-01-26 03:59:13','2018-01-26 03:59:13','<p>Theo phn tch google trends lin quan n CI/CDTheo phn tch google trends lin quan n CI/CD<br /><a href=\"https://dzone.com/storage/temp/5619859-picture1.pnghttps://dzone.com/storage/temp/5619860-picture2.png\">https://dzone.com/storage/temp/5619859-picture1.pnghttps://dzone.com/storage/temp/5619860-picture2.png</a></p><p><br /><strong>5 key qua trng trong CI/CD</strong></p><p><br /> 1.Better Quality Code</p><p>2.Better Tested Code</p><p>3.Production Snapshot</p><p>4.Early Error Detection</p><p>5.Project Confidence</p><p><br /><strong>18 pattern &amp; anti-pattern CI/CD</strong></p><p><br />Build Software at Every Change</p><p>Pattern Run a software build with every change applied to the Repository.</p><p>Anti-patterns Scheduled builds, nightly builds