o swapfile.','To swapfile cho ubuntu server','','publish','open','closed','','tao-swapfile-cho-ubuntu-server','','','2018-01-29 08:19:05','2018-01-29 08:19:05','',0,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/question/tao-swapfile-cho-ubuntu-server/',0,'question','',0),(213,4,'2018-01-29 08:19:05','2018-01-29 08:19:05','Your posted a question \"\" ','post_question','','publish','open','closed','','post_question-17','','','2018-01-29 08:19:05','2018-01-29 08:19:05','',212,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/changelog/post_question-17/',0,'changelog','',0),(214,4,'2018-01-29 08:25:52','2018-01-29 08:25:52','<p>Ch  thng thng ta s to swap file trn h thng c  cng truyn thng. s dng swap vi cc  cng SSDs c th lm cho  cng xung cp theo thi gian.</p><p>Cc bc  to swapfile:</p><div><b>Check the System for Swap Information</b></div><p></p><div><div><div>[code]<br /> sudo swapon --show<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>Nu khng c thng tin tr v th h thng hin ti khng c swap</div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>C th xem dung lng trng bng lnh</div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> free -h<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><b>Check Available Space on the Hard Drive Partition</b></div><p></p><div>Thng thng th swap nm trn mt phn vng ring bit nhng khng phi lc no ta cng c th to mt phn vng nh th.  y ta s to mt swapfile trn mt phn vng c sn.</div><p></p><div>Kim tra dung lng disk s dng:</div><p></p><div>df -h</div><p></p><div><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Output:</span></div><p></p><div><pre><code>Filesystem      Size  Used Avail Use% Mounted on<br />\nudev            238M     0  238M   0% /dev<br />\ntmpfs            49M  624K   49M   2% /run<br />\n/dev/vda1        20G  1.1G   18G   6% /<br />\ntmpfs           245M     0  245M   0% /dev/shm<br />\ntmpfs           5.0M     0  5.0M   0% /run/lock<br />\ntmpfs           245M     0  245M   0% /sys/fs/cgroup<br />\ntmpfs            49M     0   49M   0% /run/user/1001</code></pre><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><b>Create a Swap File</b></div><p></p><div>To s to swap file dung lng 1G ti th mc gc (/)</div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> sudo fallocate -l 1G /swapfile<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>Check file va to</div><p></p><div><div>ls -lh /swapfile</div><p></p></div><p></p><div><b>Enabling the Swap File</b></div><p></p><div><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">u tin cn set li quyn ch cho user root c quyn c ghi file swap</span></div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> sudo chmod 600 /swapfile<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>Mark the file as swap space by typing:</div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> sudo mkswap /swapfile<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>After marking the file, we can enable the swap file, allowing our system to start utilizing it:</div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> sudo swapon /swapfile<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><b>Make the Swap File Permanent</b></div><p></p><div>Cc bc trn ch to swap cho ln khi ng ny, nu my restart th swap s mt.  gi swap sau khi reboot ta lm nh sau:</div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>Adding the swap file to our /etc/fstab file.</div><p></p><div>Backup fstab file</div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> sudo cp /etc/fstab /etc/fstab.bak<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div>You can add the swap file information to the end of your /etc/fstab file by typing:</div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> echo \'/swapfile none swap sw 0 0\' | sudo tee -a /etc/fstab<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><b>Tweak your Swap Settings</b></div><p></p><div>C th cu hnh mt vi ty chn  swapfile t hiu nng cao</div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><b>Adjusting the Swappiness Property</b></div><p></p><div>The swappiness parameter configures how often your system swaps data out of RAM to the swap space. This is a value between 0 and 100 that represents a percentage.</div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>We can see the current swappiness value by typing:</div><p></p><div><div>cat /proc/sys/vm/swappiness</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>For a Desktop, a swappiness setting of 60 is not a bad value. For a server, you might want to move it closer to 0, ex 10.</div><p></p><div><div>sudo sysctl vm.swappiness=10</div><p></p></div><p></p><div>Gi cu hnh sau khi reboot</div><p></p><div><div>sudo vi/etc/sysctl.conf</div><p></p></div><p></p><div><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Add:<b>vm.swappiness=10</b></span></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><b>Adjusting the Cache Pressure Setting</b></div><p></p><div>Another related value that you might want to modify is the vfs_cache_pressure. This setting configures how much the system will choose to cache inode and dentry information over other data.</div><p></p><div>Xem gi tr hin ti:</div><p></p><div><div>cat /proc/sys/vm/vfs_cache_pressure</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>Set xung 50:</div><p></p><div><div>sudo sysctl vm.vfs_cache_pressure=50</div><p></p></div><p></p><div>Gi cu hnh sau khi reboot</div><p></p><div><div><div>sudo vi/etc/sysctl.conf</div><p></p></div><p></p></div><p></p><div>Add:<b>vm.vfs_cache_pressure=50</b></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Done!</span></div><p></p><p></p><p>Tham kho:<a href=\"https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-add-swap-space-on-ubuntu-16-04\">https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-add-swap-space-on-ubuntu-16-04</a></p><p></p><p></p><p></p>','RE: To swapfile cho ubuntu server','','trash','open','closed','','re-tao-swapfile-cho-ubuntu-server__trashed','','','2018-01-29 08:27:27','2018-01-29 08:27:27','',212,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/answer/re-tao-swapfile-cho-ubuntu-server/',0,'answer','',0),(215,4,'2018-01-29 08:25:52','2018-01-29 08:25:52','You answered on question \"To swapfile cho ubuntu server\"','post_answer','','publish','open','closed','','post_answer-18','','','2018-01-29 08:25:52','2018-01-29 08:25:52','',214,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/changelog/post_answer-18/',0,'changelog','',0),(216,4,'2018-01-29 08:27:12','2018-01-29 08:27:12','<p>Ch  thng thng ta s to swap file trn h thng c  cng truyn thng. s dng swap vi cc  cng SSDs c th lm cho  cng xung cp theo thi gian.</p><p>Cc bc  to swapfile:</p><div><b>Check the System for Swap Information</b></div><p></p><div><div><div>[code]<br /> sudo swapon --show<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>Nu khng c thng tin tr v th h thng hin ti khng c swap</div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>C th xem dung lng trng bng lnh</div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> free -h<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><b>Check Available Space on the Hard Drive Partition</b></div><p></p><div>Thng thng th swap nm trn mt phn vng ring bit nhng khng phi lc no ta cng c th to mt phn vng nh th.  y ta s to mt swapfile trn mt phn vng c sn.</div><p></p><div>Kim tra dung lng disk s dng:</div><p></p><div>df -h</div><p></p><div><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Output:</span></div><p></p><div><pre><code>Filesystem      Size  Used Avail Use% Mounted on<br />\nudev            238M     0  238M   0% /dev<br />\ntmpfs            49M  624K   49M   2% /run<br />\n/dev/vda1        20G  1.1G   18G   6% /<br />\ntmpfs           245M     0  245M   0% /dev/shm<br />\ntmpfs           5.0M     0  5.0M   0% /run/lock<br />\ntmpfs           245M     0  245M   0% /sys/fs/cgroup<br />\ntmpfs            49M     0   49M   0% /run/user/1001</code></pre><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><b>Create a Swap File</b></div><p></p><div>To s to swap file dung lng 1G ti th mc gc (/)</div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> sudo fallocate -l 1G /swapfile<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>Check file va to</div><p></p><div><div>ls -lh /swapfile</div><p></p></div><p></p><div><b>Enabling the Swap File</b></div><p></p><div><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">u tin cn set li quyn ch cho user root c quyn c ghi file swap</span></div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> sudo chmod 600 /swapfile<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>Mark the file as swap space by typing:</div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> sudo mkswap /swapfile<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>After marking the file, we can enable the swap file, allowing our system to start utilizing it:</div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> sudo swapon /swapfile<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><b>Make the Swap File Permanent</b></div><p></p><div>Cc bc trn ch to swap cho ln khi ng ny, nu my restart th swap s mt.  gi swap sau khi reboot ta lm nh sau:</div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>Adding the swap file to our /etc/fstab file.</div><p></p><div>Backup fstab file</div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> sudo cp /etc/fstab /etc/fstab.bak<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div>You can add the swap file information to the end of your /etc/fstab file by typing:</div><p></p><div><div>[code]<br /> echo \'/swapfile none swap sw 0 0\' | sudo tee -a /etc/fstab<br /> [/code]</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><b>Tweak your Swap Settings</b></div><p></p><div>C th cu hnh mt vi ty chn  swapfile t hiu nng cao</div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><b>Adjusting the Swappiness Property</b></div><p></p><div>The swappiness parameter configures how often your system swaps data out of RAM to the swap space. This is a value between 0 and 100 that represents a percentage.</div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>We can see the current swappiness value by typing:</div><p></p><div><div>cat /proc/sys/vm/swappiness</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>For a Desktop, a swappiness setting of 60 is not a bad value. For a server, you might want to move it closer to 0, ex 10.</div><p></p><div><div>sudo sysctl vm.swappiness=10</div><p></p></div><p></p><div>Gi cu hnh sau khi reboot</div><p></p><div><div>sudo vi/etc/sysctl.conf</div><p></p></div><p></p><div><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Add:<b>vm.swappiness=10</b></span></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><b>Adjusting the Cache Pressure Setting</b></div><p></p><div>Another related value that you might want to modify is the vfs_cache_pressure. This setting configures how much the system will choose to cache inode and dentry information over other data.</div><p></p><div>Xem gi tr hin ti:</div><p></p><div><div>cat /proc/sys/vm/vfs_cache_pressure</div><p></p></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div>Set xung 50:</div><p></p><div><div>sudo sysctl vm.vfs_cache_pressure=50</div><p></p></div><p></p><div>Gi cu hnh sau khi reboot</div><p></p><div><div><div>sudo vi/etc/sysctl.conf</div><p></p></div><p></p></div><p></p><div>Add:<b>vm.vfs_cache_pressure=50</b></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Done!</span></div><p></p><p></p><p>Tham kho:<a href=\"https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-add-swap-space-on-ubuntu-16-04\">https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-add-swap-space-on-ubuntu-16-04</a></p><p></p><p></p><p></p>','RE: To swapfile cho ubuntu server','','inherit','closed','closed','','214-revision-v1','','','2018-01-29 08:27:12','2018-01-29 08:27:12','',214,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/2018/01/29/214-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(217,4,'2018-01-29 08:27:12','2018-01-29 08:27:12','Your answer on question \"To swapfile cho ubuntu server was edited\"','edit_answer','','publish','open','closed','','edit_answer-22','','','2018-01-29 08:27:12','2018-01-29 08:27:12','',214,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/changelog/edit_answer-22/',0,'changelog','',0),(218,4,'2018-01-29 08:27:27','2018-01-29 08:27:27','Your answer on question \"To swapfile cho ubuntu server was edited\"','edit_answer','','publish','open','closed','','edit_answer-23','','','2018-01-29 08:27:27','2018-01-29 08:27:27','',214,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/changelog/edit_answer-23/',0,'changelog','',0),(219,4,'2018-01-29 08:27:59','2018-01-29 08:27:59','<div><b>Ch :</b>To swap file ch nn s dng trn cc h thng c  cng truyn thng. S dng swap file trn cc h thng c  cng SSD s lm  cng xung cp theo thi gian.</div><div></div><div><div><b>Check the System for Swap Information</b></div><div><div><div>sudo swapon --show</div></div></div><div></div><div>Nu khng c thng tin tr v th h thng hin ti khng c swap</div><div></div><div>C th xem dung lng trng bng lnh</div><div><div>free -h</div></div><div></div><div><b>Check Available Space on the Hard Drive Partition</b></div><div>Thng thng th swap nm trn mt phn vng ring bit nhng khng phi lc no ta cng c th to mt phn vng nh th.  y ta s to mt swapfile trn mt phn vng c sn.</div><div>Kim tra dung lng disk s dng:</div><div>df -h</div><div><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Output:</span></div><div><pre><code>Filesystem      Size  Used Avail Use% Mounted on\nudev            238M     0  238M   0% /dev\ntmpfs            49M  624K   49M   2% /run\n/dev/vda1        20G  1.1G   18G   6% /\ntmpfs           245M     0  245M   0% /dev/shm\ntmpfs           5.0M     0  5.0M   0% /run/lock\ntmpfs           245M     0  245M   0% /sys/fs/cgroup\ntmpfs            49M     0   49M   0% /run/user/1001</code></pre></div><div></div><div><b>Create a Swap File</b></div><div>To s to swap file dung lng 1G ti th mc gc (/)</div><div><div>sudo fallocate -l 1G /swapfile</div></div><div></div><div>Check file va to</div><div><div>ls -lh /swapfile</div></div><div><b>Enabling the Swap File</b></div><div><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">u tin cn set li quyn ch cho user root c quyn c ghi file swap</span></div><div><div>sudo chmod 600 /swapfile</div></div><div></div><div>Mark the file as swap space by typing:</div><div><div>sudo mkswap /swapfile</div></div><div></div><div>After marking the file, we can enable the swap file, allowing our system to start utilizing it:</div><div><div>sudo swapon /swapfile</div></div><div></div><div><b>Make the Swap File Permanent</b></div><div>Cc bc trn ch to swap cho ln khi ng ny, nu my restart th swap s mt.  gi swap sau khi reboot ta lm nh sau:</div><div></div><div>Adding the swap file to our /etc/fstab file.</div><div>Backup fstab file</div><div><div>sudo cp /etc/fstab /etc/fstab.bak</div></div><div>You can add the swap file information to the end of your /etc/fstab file by typing:</div><div><div>echo \'/swapfile none swap sw 0 0\' | sudo tee -a /etc/fstab</div></div><div></div><div><b>Tweak your Swap Settings</b></div><div>C th cu hnh mt vi ty chn  swapfile t hiu nng cao</div><div></div><div><b>Adjusting the Swappiness Property</b></div><div>The swappiness parameter configures how often your system swaps data out of RAM to the swap space. This is a value between 0 and 100 that represents a percentage.</div><div></div><div></div><div>We can see the current swappiness value by typing:</div><div><div>cat /proc/sys/vm/swappiness</div></div><div></div><div>For a Desktop, a swappiness setting of 60 is not a bad value. For a server, you might want to move it closer to 0, ex 10.</div><div><div>sudo sysctl vm.swappiness=10</div></div><div>Gi cu hnh sau khi reboot</div><div><div>sudo vi/etc/sysctl.conf</div></div><div><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Add:<b>vm.swappiness=10</b></span></div><div></div><div><b>Adjusting the Cache Pressure Setting</b></div><div>Another related value that you might want to modify is the vfs_cache_pressure. This setting configures how much the system will choose to cache inode and dentry information over other data.</div><div>Xem gi tr hin ti:</div><div><div>cat /proc/sys/vm/vfs_cache_pressure</div></div><div></div><div>Set xung 50:</div><div><div>sudo sysctl vm.vfs_cache_pressure=50</div></div><div>Gi cu hnh sau khi reboot</div><div><div><div>sudo vi/etc/sysctl.conf</div></div></div><div>Add:<b>vm.vfs_cache_pressure=50</b></div><div></div><div><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Done!</span></div></div><p></p><div>Tham kho:<a href=\"https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-add-swap-space-on-ubuntu-16-04\">https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-add-swap-space-on-ubuntu-16-04</a></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div></div>','RE: To swapfile cho ubuntu server','','publish','open','closed','','re-tao-swapfile-cho-ubuntu-server','','','2018-01-29 08:30:05','2018-01-29 08:30:05','',212,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/answer/re-tao-swapfile-cho-ubuntu-server/',0,'answer','',0),(220,4,'2018-01-29 08:27:59','2018-01-29 08:27:59','You answered on question \"To swapfile cho ubuntu server\"','post_answer','','publish','open','closed','','post_answer-19','','','2018-01-29 08:27:59','2018-01-29 08:27:59','',219,'http://blog.sigma-global.net/changelog/post_answer-19/',0,'changelog','',0),(221,4,'2018-01-29 08:30:05','2018-01-29 08:30:05','<div><b>Ch :</b>To swap file ch nn s dng trn cc h thng c  cng truyn thng. S dng swap file trn cc h thng c  cng SSD s lm  cng xung cp theo thi gian.</div><div></div><div><div><b>Check the System for Swap Information</b></div><div><div><div>sudo swapon --show</div></div></div><div></div><div>Nu khng c thng tin tr v th h thng hin ti khng c swap</div><div></div><div>C th xem dung lng trng bng lnh</div><div><div>free -h</div></div><div></div><div><b>Check Available Space on the Hard Drive Partition</b></div><div>Thng thng th swap nm trn mt phn vng ring bit nhng khng phi lc no ta cng c th to mt